FILE PATH: .github/workflows/ci.yml
CONTENT: 

```yaml
name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v3
        with:
          node-version: '16'
          cache: 'npm'
      - name: Install dependencies
        run: npm ci
      - name: Run Tests
        run: npm test
      - name: Deploy
        uses: vercel/vercel-action@v1.0.1
        with:
          token: ${{ secrets.VERCEL_TOKEN }}
          args: --prod
```

FILE PATH: README.md
CONTENT: 

```markdown
# Web Proxy

This is a simple web proxy that allows you to access websites that may be blocked in your region.

## Usage

To use the proxy, simply enter the URL of the website you want to access into the form on the homepage and click "Submit". The proxy will then fetch the website and display it in your browser.

## Deployment

To deploy the proxy to Vercel, you will need to create a new project and add the following environment variables:

- `VERCEL_VERCEL_TOKEN`: Your Vercel token
- `NODE_PORT`: The port that the proxy will listen on (default: 3000)

Once you have added these environment variables, you can deploy the proxy by clicking the "Deploy" button in the Vercel dashboard.
```